<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="AppDiffEVT" checkit-title="Extreme Value Theorem">
    <statement>
        <p> 
Explain how to find the absolute minimum and absolute maximum values of the
function <m>f(x)=2 \, x^{3} - 39 \, x^{2} + 240 \, x - 81</m> on the interval <m>[2,7]</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
The absolute extrema may occur at these <m>x</m>-values:
<m>2, 5, 7</m>.
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li><p><m>f(2)=259</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(5)=394</m></p></li>
            <li><p><m>f(7)=374</m></p></li>
        </ul>
        <p>
Thus the absolute minimum is <m>259</m> and the absolute
maximum is <m>394</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
(The value <m>f(8)=367</m>
is ignored as <m>8</m> isn't in the given interval.)
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
